quran[86]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,About what do they question one another
  78,2,About the Great Tiding
  78,3,regarding which they differ
  78,4,"Nay, but they will know"
  78,5,Then indeed they will know
  78,6,Did We not make the earth a resting place
  78,7,and the mountains stakes
  78,8,and create you in pairs
  78,9,and make your sleep repose
  78,10,and make the night a garment
  78,11,and the day for livelihood
  78,12,"And [did We not] build above you seven firmaments"
  78,13,and make a radiant lamp
  78,14,and send down water pouring from the rain clouds
  78,15,that We might produce grain and plants thereby
  78,16,and luxuriant gardens
  78,17,Truly the Day of Division is a Moment Appointed
  78,18,a day when the trumpet is blown and you come forth in throngs
  78,19,and the sky is opened as if it were gates
  78,20,and the mountains are set in motion as if they were a mirage
  78,21,Truly Hell lies in ambush
  78,22,a place unto which the rebellious return
  78,23,to tarry therein for ages
  78,24,They taste therein neither coolness nor drink
  78,25,"save boiling liquid and a cold, murky fluid"
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,Truly they anticipated not a reckoning
  78,28,and denied Our signs with utter denial
  78,29,And everything have We recorded in a book
  78,30,So taste! For We shall not increase you in aught but punishment
  78,31,Truly the reverent shall have a place of triumph
  78,32,gardens and vineyards
  78,33,buxom maidens of like age
  78,34,and an overflowing cup
  78,35,They hear therein neither idle talk nor lying—
  78,36,"a recompense from thy Lord, a gift abounding—"
  78,37,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth, and whatsoever is between them, the Compassionate, Whom they have no power to address"
  78,38,"That Day the Spirit and the angels stand in rows, none speaking, save one whom the Compassionate permits and who speaks aright"
  78,39,"That is the True Day. So let whosoever will, take a path of return unto his Lord"
  78,40,"Truly We have warned you of a punishment nigh, on a day when a man beholds what his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever says, “Oh, would that I were dust!”"
  79,1,By those that wrest violently
  79,2,by those that draw out quickly
  79,3,by those that glide serenely
  79,4,"by those that race to the fore, outstripping"
  79,5,and by those that govern affairs
  79,6,on the Day when the quaker quakes
  79,7,and the successor follows upon it
  79,8,Hearts that Day shall tremble
  79,9,with eyes humbled
  79,10,"They will say, “Are we to be restored as we were before"
  79,11,What! When we have become decayed bones?”
  79,12,"They say, “This, then, would be a ruinous return!”"
  79,13,Yet it shall be but a single cry
  79,14,"then, behold, they will be upon a wide expanse"
  79,15,Hast thou heard tell of Moses
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him in the holy valley of ?uwa
  79,17,“Go unto Pharaoh! Truly he has rebelled
  79,18,"And say, ‘Dost thou wish to be purified"
  79,19,and that I guide thee to thy Lord that thou mightest have fear?’”
  79,20,Then he showed him the greatest sign
  79,21,But he denied and disobeyed
  79,22,"Then turned his back, moving swiftly"
  79,23,Then he gathered and proclaimed
  79,24,"and said, “I am your lord most high.”"
  79,25,So God seized him with a punishment exemplary in the Hereafter and in this world
  79,26,Truly in that is a lesson for whosoever fears
  79,27,Are you more difficult to create or the sky that He has built
  79,28,He raised high its canopy and fashioned it
  79,29,"darkened its night, and brought forth its day"
  79,30,And after that He spread out the earth
  79,31,From it He brought forth its water and its pastures
  79,32,and the mountains He set firm
  79,33,as sustenance for you and for your flocks
  79,34,So when the Great Calamity befalls—
  79,35,a day when man shall remember that for which he endeavored
  79,36,and Hellfire is made visible for one who sees—
  79,37,as for one who rebels
  79,38,and prefers the life of this world
  79,39,truly Hellfire is the refuge
  79,40,As for one who fears standing before his Lord and forbids the soul from caprice
  79,41,truly the Garden is the refuge
  79,42,"They ask thee about the Hour, “When shall it set in?”"
  79,43,What hast thou to do with mentioning it
  79,44,"Unto thy Lord is [knowledge of] the end thereof"
  79,45,Thou art but a warner for whosoever fears it
  79,46,"The Day they see it, it will be as if they had tarried but an evening or the morning thereof"